d%20earned%20about%20%2420%2C000.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20decided%20that%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20live%20in%20a%20big%20house%20again%2C%20and%20would%20instead%20rent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%202016%2C%20I%20saw%20an%20episode%20of%20the%20television%20show%20%26quot%3BTiny%20House%20Nation%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20was%20inspired%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wanted%20a%20tiny%20house%20of%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20year%2C%20I%20flew%20to%20Colorado%20Springs%20to%20attend%20my%20first%20tiny-home%20jamboree.%20At%20the%20gathering%2C%20I%20met%20a%20female%20builder%20that%20agreed%20to%20help%20me%20construct%20my%20own%20tiny%20home%2C%20a%20two-bedroom%20unit%20that%20cost%20%2457%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20construction%20was%20completed%2C%20I%20had%20to%20find%20somewhere%20to%20park%20the%20home%20legally.%20After%20a%20few%20let%20downs%2C%20I%20heard%20about%20a%20gentleman%20from%20Decatur%2C%20Texas%2C%20who%20was%20building%20a%20tiny-home%20village%20and%20charging%20people%20%24450%20to%20rent%20land.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20I%20moved%20onto%20his%20property.%20I%20was%20the%20very%20first%20tiny-houser.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20inspired%20to%20create%20my%20own%20tiny-home%20village%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%2C%20all%20seven%20of%20the%20village's%20lots%20were%20full%20and%20I%20grew%20to%20really%20love%20the%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20around%202019%2C%20I%20began%20thinking%20more%20about%20my%20future%20and%20financial%20health.%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20support%20myself%20through%20retirement%20solely%20on%20the%20funds%20made%20available%20from%20my%20401(k)%20and%20social%20security.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Bird's%20Nest%20tiny-home%20village.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c913c8048ff200190edc84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Bird's%20Nest%20tiny-home%20village.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Robyn%20Yerian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20reading%20articles%20on%20how%20to%20make%20passive%20income%20in%20retirement.%20During%20this%20time%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20that%20worked%20in%20finance%20encouraged%20me%20to%20purchase%20land%20that%20I%20could%20someday%20rent%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20lot%20of%20searching%2C%20I%20bought%20five%20acres%20in%20Cumby%2C%20Texas%2C%20for%20%2435%2C000.%20To%20afford%20the%20purchase%2C%20I%20withdrew%20money%20from%20my%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20land%20initially%20had%20no%20water%20and%20electricity.%20It%20also%20needed%20to%20be%20excavated%20and%20required%20a%20new%20septic%20system.%20I%20spent%20%24100%2C000%20developing%20the%20property.%20Once%20updates%20were%20completed%2C%20I%20moved%20my%20tiny%20home%20from%20Decatur%20to%20Cumby%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20developed%20the%20concept%20for%20The%20Bird's%20Nest%2C%20a%20women-only%2C%20tiny-home%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20created%20The%20Bird's%20Nest%20to%20support%20women%20that%20are%20in%20need%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bird's%20Nest%20operates%20similarly%20to%20an%20RV%20park.%20Tenants%20bring%20their%20own%20tiny%20homes%20and%20park%20it%20in%20one%20of%20my%2014%20lots.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Bird's%20Nest%20logo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c90c5fcf0778001968623e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Bird's%20Nest%20logo.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Robyn%20Yerian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20of%20the%20lots%20are%20currently%20occupied%2C%20while%20a%20few%20of%20the%20others%20have%20buildings%20on%20them%20that%20are%20being%20used%20as%20a%20party%20pad%2C%20work%20space%2C%20and%20a%20community%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20wanted%20the%20community%20to%20be%20only%20for%20senior%20women%2C%20those%20over%20the%20age%20of%2055%20that%20did%20not%20have%20any%20children.%20But%20I%20started%20getting%20calls%20from%20women%20of%20all%20ages%20that%20were%20interested%20in%20the%20village.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20time%20they%20were%20women%20who%20were%20escaping%20abusive%20situations%20or%20those%20who%20were%20recently%20divorced%20that%20needed%20an%20affordable%20place%20to%20live.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20to%20myself%2C%20if%20I%20can%20help%20these%20women%2C%20why%20not%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20want%20the%20village%20to%20be%20an%20affordable%20housing%20option%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERent%20at%20The%20Bird's%20Nest%20is%20only%20%24450%20a%20month.%20I%20tell%20every%20person%20that%20comes%20here%20that%20I'm%20never%20going%20to%20raise%20the%20rent%20and%20I%20mean%20it.%20I've%20even%20offered%20reduced%20prices%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20women%20that%20were%20in%20bad%20financial%20situations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20that's%20how%20you%20build%20a%20community%20%E2%80%94%20showing%20others%20they%20can%20count%20on%20you%20and%20you%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20this%20month%2C%20one%20of%20my%20tenants%20is%20having%20her%20knee%20replaced.%20All%20of%20the%20women%20at%20The%20Bird's%20Nest%20have%20agreed%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%20as%20she%20recovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20tiny-home%20at%20The%20Bird's%20Nest.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c90dd1048ff200190ed4e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Barbie-themed%20tiny%20home%20at%20The%20Bird's%20Nest.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Robyn%20Yerian%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Bird's%20Nest%20focuses%20on%20empowering%20women%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20The%20Bird's%20Nest%20hosted%20its%20first-