nd%20had%20objects%20thrown%20at%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmichael-burry-big-short-housing-bubble-crash-gamestop-meme-stock-2021-10%5C%22%3EMichael%20Burry%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Short%26quot%3B%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-indicator-ai-tech-stock-market-outlook-forecast-crash-2023-7%5C%22%3EWarren%20Buffett%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20Internet%20bubble%2C%20it%20takes%20extraordinary%20conviction%20to%20stick%20to%20your%20guns%20when%20virtually%20everyone%20says%20you're%20wrong%2C%20and%20dismisses%20your%20contrarian%20stance%20as%20stubborn%20foolishness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Rosenberg%2C%20a%20leading%20economist%20who%20called%20both%20the%20dot-com%20and%20housing%20crashes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-dow-streak-rosenberg-recession-inflation-fomo-fed-2023-7%5C%22%3Eremains%20fully%20convinced%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20headed%20for%20a%20recession.%20He%20doubled%20down%20on%20his%20forecast%20in%20a%20client%20memo%20titled%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I'm%20Not%20Turning%20Soft%26quot%3B%20on%20Monday%20%E2%80%94%20and%20shared%20a%20bunch%20of%20colorful%20anecdotes%20about%20previous%20pushback%20he's%20resisted%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EI%20was%20asked%20all%20through%202007%20when%20I%20was%20at%20Merrill%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20is%20this%20recession%20you've%20been%20calling%20for%2C%C2%A0Rosenberg%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20same%20salespeople%20on%20the%20equity%20desk%20who%20refused%20to%20take%20me%20to%20see%20clients%20that%20year%20became%20my%20best%20friends%20in%202008%20(they%20know%20who%20they%20are).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EI%20almost%20got%20fired%20twice%20for%20my%20calls%20in%202007%20but%20my%20Institutional%20Investor%20All-Star%20rankings%20saved%20my%20skin.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202007%2C%20I%20had%20a%20CIO%20at%20a%20famed%20Houston-based%20mutual%20fund%20storm%20out%20of%20a%20meeting%20I%20gave%20and%20he%20scolded%20me%20as%20he%20exited%20the%20boardroom%20(%26quot%3Byou%20have%20no%20clue%20about%20the%20housing%20market%20or%20the%20economy%20for%20that%20matter%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EI%20had%20the%20head%20of%20Merrill's%20fixed-income%20sales%20physically%20throw%20my%20presentation%20package%20at%20me%20at%20an%20internal%20meeting%20and%20told%20me%20in%20front%20of%20about%2030%20people%20that%20I%20was%20the%20worst%20Fed-watcher%20he%20ever%20saw.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EOne%20time%2C%20when%20I%20was%20walking%20around%20the%20trading%20floor%2C%20this%20guy%20called%20me%20over%20and%20handed%20me%20the%20phone%20and%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20client%20but%20it%20was%20his%20wife%20on%20the%20line%2C%20and%20she%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20husband%20asked%20me%20to%20ask%20you%20why%20it%20is%20you%20are%20so%20useless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EI%20have%20one%20client%2C%20who%20shall%20remain%20nameless%20obviously%2C%20who%20hurls%20insults%20at%20me%20every%20single%20day.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EI%20was%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bskunk%20at%20the%20picnic%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bclass%20clown%26quot%3B%20in%202007%20(and%20in%202000%20as%20well%20when%20I%20was%20called%20a%20%26quot%3BLuddite%26quot%3B%20because%20I%20didn't%20understand%20how%20the%20Internet%20defeated%20the%20business%20cycle)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3EBehind%20the%20recession%20call%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20explained%20in%20his%20memo%20why%20he's%20not%20caving%20in%20to%20peer%20pressure%20and%20buying%20into%20the%20market%20narrative.%20Here%20are%20the%20key%20points%20he%20made%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20GDP%20may%20have%20climbed%202.4%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20but%20the%20economy%20grew%20by%20a%20similar%20percentage%20in%20the%20quarter%20preceding%20both%20the%202001%20and%202007-2009%20recessions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20interest-rate%20hikes%20will%20have%20delayed%2C%20negative%20impacts%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERecession%20indicators%20including%20the%20inverted%20yield%20curve%2C%20The%20Conference%20Board's%20Leading%20Economic%20Index%2C%20and%20the%20New%20York%20Fed's%20recession%20model%20are%20still%20flashing%20red.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20still%20well%20within%20the%20ranges%20of%20the%20past%20for%20each%20indicator%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmericans%20are%20still%20spending%20the%20savings%20they%20accumulated%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20fiscal%20packages%20have%20shored%20up%20the%20economy.%20Those%20factors%20have%20delayed%20the%20recession's%20onset.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20a%20big%20gap%20between%20the%20Conference%20Board's%20coincident%20and%20leading%20indexes%2C%20which%20has%20reliably%20been%20the%20case%20prior%20to%20previous%20recessions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20stock%20market's%20rally%20this%20year%20isn't%20surprising%2C%20as%20bear%20markets%20often%20start%20with%20a%20sharp%20fall%2C%20then%20stage%20a%20short-lived%20rally%2C%20before%20embarking%20on%20a%20protracted%20decline.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3ERefusing%20to%20back%20down%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20underlined%20in%20his%20memo%20that%20he%20isn't%20cowed%20by%20the%20opposition%20to%20his%20recession%20forecast%2C%20as%20it's%20nothing%20he%20hasn't%20seen%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20smugness%20and%20complacency%20are%20ubiquitous%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20chief%20North%20American%20economist%20at%20Merrill%20Lynch%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20I%20can%20say%20is%20that%20this%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20I%20have%20been%20early%20on%20the%20call%2C%20and%20certain