s%20of%20minority%20experience.%20In%20particular%2C%20there%20is%20the%20discomfiting%20scene%20of%20Alif%20and%20Tahira%20undergoing%20a%20derogatory%20interrogation%20while%20trying%20to%20rent%20a%20flat.%20At%20another%20time%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20told%20that%20Tahira%20dislikes%20the%20assumption%2C%20especially%20during%20Eid%2C%20that%20because%20she%20is%20Muslim%20and%20a%20woman%20she%20must%20be%20a%20great%20cook.%20%E2%80%9CIs%20this%20all%20we%20are%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asks%20Alif.%20%E2%80%9CBawarchis%3F%20Poetry-spouting%20fools%20with%20minced%20mutton%20coming%20out%20of%20our%20ears%2C%20thinking%20only%20of%20Allah%20and%20pining%20only%20for%20bahisht%20between%20mouthfuls%20of%20zafrani%20pulao%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20flip%20side%20of%20this%20is%20that%20there%20are%20stretches%20in%20which%20very%20little%20happens%20from%20a%20novelistic%20point%20of%20view.%20Instead%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHistory%E2%80%99s%20Angel%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20relies%20on%20creating%20empathy%20through%20well-rounded%20characters%20to%20propel%20itself%20forward%20by%20sinuous%20sentences.%20Because%20Alif%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20rather%20read%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Discovery%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20than%20discover%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20his%20complaisant%20nature%20isn%E2%80%99t%20entirely%20up%20to%20the%20job%20of%20sustaining%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20one%20stage%2C%20Alif%20politely%20informs%20his%20overly%20patriotic%20school%20principal%20while%20breaking%20into%20a%20sweat%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20a%20Muslim%20history%20of%20India%E2%80%A6try%20separating%20Muslims%20from%20Hindus%20in%20this%20way%20when%20you%20go%20into%20the%20past%20of%20this%20country%20and%20all%20you%20find%20are%20entanglements%E2%80%9D.%20Though%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20national%20destiny%20frightens%20him%2C%20he%20has%20little%20choice%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20to%20stay%20with%20the%20moderate%20hopes%20and%20incremental%20changes%20that%20democratic%20statehood%20offers%20till%20they%20come%20up%20with%20a%20better%20substitute%20for%20it%2C%20which%20no%20one%20has%20so%20far%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20such%20ways%2C%20he%20personifies%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20title%2C%20taken%20from%20Walter%20Benjamin%E2%80%99s%20conception%20of%20the%20angel%20of%20history%2C%20whose%20face%20is%20turned%20towards%20the%20past%20with%20the%20wreckage%20of%20catastrophe%20piled%20at%20his%20feet.%20The%20angel%20wants%20to%20restore%20what%20has%20been%20smashed%20but%20cannot%2C%20because%20his%20wings%20are%20entangled%20in%20the%20storm%20of%20progress%20that%20propels%20him%20forward.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20her%20careful%20delineation%20of%20such%20a%20predicament%2C%20Anjum%20Hasan%20asks%20us%20to%20consider%20what%20is%20gained%20and%20what%20is%20lost%20in%20the%20face%20of%20this%20nationalistic%20storm.%20The%20novel%20is%2C%20to%20borrow%20from%20Susan%20Sontag%2C%20an%20education%20of%20the%20heart.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fsanjay-sipahimalani%5C%22%3ESanjay%20Sipahimalani%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20Mumbai-based%20writer%20and%20reviewer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690886307000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01155958%2FDAEFC20B-9E9E-4268-B054-A64E9B81.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fanjum-hasan-historys-angel-muslim-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anjum%20Hasan%E2%80%99s%20book%20'History%E2%80%99s%20Angel'%20immerses%20the%20reader%20in%20a%20range%20of%20quotidian%20minority%20experiences.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fanjum-hasan-historys-angel-muslim-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpU