tion%20Technology%20had%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fopposition-activists-raise-alarm-as-modi-govt-gets-ready-to-pass-data-protection-bill%5C%22%3Etold%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fopposition-activists-raise-alarm-as-modi-govt-gets-ready-to-pass-data-protection-bill%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20the%20committee%20had%20on%20July%2026%20adopted%20a%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Citizen%E2%80%99s%20data%20security%20and%20privacy%E2%80%99.%20The%20report%20examines%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20and%20contains%20recommendations%20of%20the%20committee%20on%20the%20same.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20opposition%20members%20in%20the%20committee%20do%20not%20approve%20of%20the%20report%2C%20mainly%20because%2C%20according%20to%20them%20the%20report%20was%20prepared%20by%20the%20committee%20by%20bypassing%20parliamentary%20procedure%20which%20requires%20a%20Bill%20to%20be%20first%20introduced%20in%20either%20House%20of%20parliament%20before%20it%20can%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20standing%20committee%20for%20any%20report%20to%20be%20tabled%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20members%20also%20allege%20that%20they%20have%20not%20seen%20the%20final%20Bill%20and%20had%20very%20little%20time%20with%20the%20report%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBrittas%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20had%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20committee%20members%20were%20given%20a%20draft%20of%20the%20report%2024%20hours%20before%20the%20meeting%20on%20July%2026%2C%20but%20not%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20cannot%20give%20the%20Bill.%20Because%20the%20Bill%20approved%20by%20the%20Union%20cabinet%20has%20not%20seen%20the%20light%20of%20the%20day%20so%20far%2C%E2%80%9D%20Brittas%20had%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFurthermore%2C%20how%20can%20they%20give%20the%20Bill%20if%20the%20government%20of%20India%20has%20not%20introduced%20the%20Bill%20in%20parliament%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrinamool%20Congress%20MP%20Jawhar%20Sircar%2C%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20had%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20opposition%20members%20decided%20to%20walk%20out%20of%20the%20meeting%2C%20where%20they%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20supposed%20to%20endorse%20the%20report%20without%20having%20seen%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20letter%20to%20the%20Speaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBrittas%20subsequently%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20on%20July%2028%2C%20asking%20him%20to%20not%20give%20permission%20to%20lay%20the%20report%20of%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20in%20parliament.%20He%20asked%20that%20it%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20tweet%20today%2C%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20Rajeev%20Chandrashekhar%20said%20what%20the%20CPI(M)%20MP%20had%20tweeted%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3Emisinformation%20and%20completely%20wrong.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%9E%A1%EF%B8%8FThis%20is%20misinformation%20and%20completely%20wrong.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%9E%A1%EF%B8%8FNo%20bill%20including%20the%20proposed%20DPDP%20(Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill)%20can%20be%20referred%20to%20any%20committee%20unless%20it%20is%20done%20so%20by%20Parliament%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%9E%A1%EF%B8%8FIn%20turn%2C%20the%20bill%20can%20be%20only%20referred%20to%20committee%20AFTER%20the%20Cabinet-approved%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FYJ7PnE9FsW%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FYJ7PnE9FsW%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20%F0%9F%87%AE%F0%9F%87%B3%20(%40Rajeev_GoI)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRajeev_GoI%2Fstatus%2F1686206764654759937%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%201%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrashekhar%20in%20his%20tweet%20claimed%20that%20no%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20proposed%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20can%20be%20referred%20to%20any%20committee%20unless%20it%20is%20done%20so%20by%20parliament.%20He%20further%20claimed%20that%20a%20Bill%20can%20be%20only%20referred%20to%20committee%20after%20the%20Cabinet-approved%20Bill%20is%20introduced%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Bill%20has%20not%20been%20introduced%20in%20parliament%2C%20Chandrashekhar%20said%20that%20the%20question%20of%20considering%20it%20in%20committee%20does%20not%20arise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResponding%20to%20Chandrashekhar%E2%80%99s%20tweet%2C%20Brittas%20said%20that%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20committee%20he%20had%20seen%20the%20report%20%E2%80%93%20unlike%20Chandrashekhar.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20report%20is%20on%20a%20Bill%20that%20has%20been%20approved%20by%20the%20Cabinet%20and%20yet%20not%20introduced%20in%20the%20House%20or%20referred%20to%20the%20committee%20is%20what%20led%20opposition%20members%20in%20the%20committee%20to%20stage%20a%20walkout.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBrittas%20also%20said%20that%20this%20report%20was%20%E2%80%9Cprepared%20before%20seeing%20the%20final%20Bill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20will%20be%20tabled%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20%5BChandrashekhar%5D%20just%20endorsed%20my%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20Brittas%20said%20in%20his%20tweet%20responding%20to%20the%20minister.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThanks%20hon%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRajeev_GoI%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40Rajeev_GoI%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20responding%20to%20my%20tweet.%20You%20just%20endorsed%20my%20position.%20I%20am%20sure%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20seen%20the%20report%20where%20as%20I%20have%20%E2%80%94%20being%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Committee.%201%2F3%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FKartiPC%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40KartiPC%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMahuaMoitra%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40MahuaMoitra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FShashiTharoor%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40ShashiTharoor%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThamizhachiTh%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40ThamizhachiTh%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjawharsircar%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40jawharsircar%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FkzihwZ2QP2%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FkzihwZ2QP2%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20John%20Brittas%20(%40JohnBrittas)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJohnBrittas%2Fstatus%2F1686233930360373248%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%201%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CRuling%20party%20members%20in%20the%20Committee%20flouted%20norms%20and%20are%20in%20the%20wrong%2C%E2%80%9D%20Brittas%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20Speaker%20accessed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EBrittas%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20urging%20him%20to%20send%20the%20report%20back%20to%20the%20committee%2C%20said%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eimperative%20to%20note%20that%20the%20said%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20had%20neither%20been%20introduced%20before%20either%20of%20the%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20till%20date.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBrittas%20added%20that%20it%20was%20not%20referred%20to%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20by%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20the%20Speaker%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20for%20examination%E2%80%9D%20either.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBrittas%20said%20that%20under%20Rules%20331E%20(1)%20(b)%2C%20331H%20(a)%20and%20331H%20(b)%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20Rules%20and%20Rules%20270%20(b)%20%26amp%3B%20273%20(a)%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Rules%2C%20the%20Standing%20Committees%20are%20explicitly%20prohibited%20from%20examining%20any%20Bills%20that%20have%20not%20been%20referred%20to%20them%20by%20the%20Chairman%20or%20the%20Speaker%20after%20their%20introduction%20in%20either%20House.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHence%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20above%20Report%20of%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Communications%20and%20Information%20Technology%2C%20said%20to%20be%20adopted%20on%2026th%20July%202023%2C%20is%20void%20ab%20initio%20and%20is%20ultra%20vires%20of%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20conferred%20by%20the%20Rules.%20The%20Rules%20proscribe%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20from%20examining%20such%20a%20yet%20to%20be%20introduced%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20states.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20can%20be%20found%20beyond%20an%20iota%20of%20doubt%20that%20the%20impetuous%20action%20of%20the%20Committee%20in%20including%20comments%20and%20recommendations%20on%20this%20Bill%20is%20far%20beyond%20its%20jurisdiction%20and%20as%20such%2C%20rendering%20the%20Report%20liable%20to%20be%20nullified.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDhankhar%20says%20action%20is%20within%20committee%E2%80%99s%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Brittas%20stood%20up%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20to%20bring%20a%20point%20of%20order%20to%20bring%20the%20matter%20to%20Chairman%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%E2%80%99s%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20report%20which%20has%20been%20presented%20on%20the%20Digital%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20which%20has%20been%20approved%20by%20the%20Cabinet%20but%20not%20introduced%20in%20the%20House%20nor%20referred%20to%20the%20standing%20committee.%20The%20Standing%20Committee%20has%20overstepped%20and%20it%20is%20beyond%20their%20jurisdiction%20breaching%20your%20authority%20and%20the%20authority%20of%20this%20house%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Brittas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhankar%20however%20said%20that%20it%20is%20the%20right%20of%20the%20committee%20to%20place%20a%20report.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20rest%20will%20follow%20in%20accordance%20with%20rules.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhankar%20added%20that%20Brittas%E2%80%99%20point%20of%20order%20was%20devoid%20of%20any%20merit.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690875198000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01125954%2FScreenshot-2023-08-01-at-12.59.1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjohn-brittas-data-protection-bill-panel-opposition-parliament%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CPI(M)%20MP%20John%20Brittas%20wrote%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20asking%20him%20to%20refuse%20permission%20to%20table%20a%20report%20and%20send%20it%20back%20to%20the%20committee.%20The%20government%20has%20claimed%20this%20cannot%20be%20done.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjohn-brittas-data-protection-bill-panel-opposition-parliament%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Debate%20on%20no-trust%20