e%20together%20in%202023%20for%20'Jailer'.%20Nelson%20Dilipkumar%20had%20approached%20Mammooty%20to%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20film%20which%20is%20now%20played%20by%20Malayalam%20actor%20Vinayakan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22etimes.in%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftamil%2Fmovies%2Fnews%2Fmammootty-was-approached-to-play-a-role-in-rajinikanths-jailer-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F102304112.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Cycle%20Mechanics%20Helped%20India%20Move%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01123038%2FC4.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20the%20seventh%20in%20a%20series%20on%20the%20history%20of%20labour%20in%20India.%20The%20first%20part%20dealt%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fcarpentry-in-colonial-india%5C%22%3Ecarpenters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20second%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-colonial-history-contributed-to-the-socio-economic-marginalisation-of-indian-tailors%5C%22%3Etailors%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20third%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fthe-invisible-women-of-colonial-indias-textile-industry%5C%22%3Etextile%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20colonial%20India%2C%20the%20fourth%20with%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fperfume-workers-attar-colonial-india%5C%22%3Eartisans%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20attar%20industry%2C%20the%20fifth%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fprinting-press-modern-india-history-compositors-proofreaders%5C%22%3Eworkers%20in%20the%20book%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20sixth%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fkaghazis-india-papermaking-industry%5C%22%3Eworkers%20in%20the%20papermaking%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20much%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20India%20moved%20on%20bicycles%20and%20bicycles%20were%20an%20integral%20item%20of%20households%2C%20individual%20possessions%20and%20government%20offices.%20Bicycles%20are%20still%20an%20important%20part%20of%20mobility%20in%20India%2C%20but%20they%20have%20been%20increasingly%20displaced%20by%20motorcycles%2C%20cars%20and%20motorised%20public%20transport.%20As%20a%20vehicle%20of%20the%20masses%2C%20the%20bicycle%20nonetheless%20continues%20to%20provide%20an%20accessible%20form%20of%20mobility%20for%20people%20across%20a%20range%20of%20social%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlongside%20the%20bicycle%20revolution%20came%20the%20rise%20of%20new%20forms%20of%20labour%20and%20new%20mechanical%20trades.%20Repair%20is%20often%20overlooked%20as%20a%20form%20of%20artisanship%20and%20craft%2C%20but%20cycle%20repair%20workers%2C%20who%20can%20still%20be%20found%20in%20small%20workshops%20and%20along%20the%20pavement%20of%20many%20Indian%20towns%20and%20metros%2C%20kept%20India%20moving%20for%20many%20decades.%20We%20all%20could%20tell%20stories%20of%20our%20bicycles%20and%20struggles%20with%20their%20breakdown.%20More%20than%20bicycle%20producers%2C%20we%20are%20fascinated%20by%20the%20neglected%20histories%20of%20those%20who%20repaired%20our%20bicycles%20and%20returned%20our%20suspended%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earliest%20Indian%20cycle%20mechanics%20repaired%20imported%20bicycles%2C%20while%20the%20rapid%20expansion%20of%20Indian%20cycle%20production%20from%20the%20mid%2020th%20century%20sparked%20even%20greater%20demand%20for%20their%20skills.%20Historians%20David%20Arnold%20and%20Erich%20Dewald%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fcomparative-studies-in-society-and-history%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fcycles-of-empowerment-the-bicycle-and-everyday-technology-in-colonial-india-and-vietnam%2FCD3D44C2AEB5E084BBA7080AF25D51D9%5C%22%3Ecalculate%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20nearly%202.5%20million%20bicycles%20were%20imported%20to%20India%20between%201910%20and%201946%2C%20making%20the%20yearly%20average%20about%2070%2C000.%20They%20further%20counted%20that%20nearly%201.2%20million%20bicycles%20entered%20independent%20India%20just%20between%201947-48%20and%201951-52.%20India%20manufacturer%20Sudhir%20Kumar%20Sen%20began%20producing%20bicycles%20in%20India%20after%20Independence%20by%20doing%20a%20tie-up%20with%20Nottingham%20based%20Raleigh%20Bicycle%20Company%20which%20produced%20the%20famous%20%E2%80%9CRobin%20Hood%E2%80%9D%20bicycles.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Janaki%20Das%20Kapur%20established%20the%20famous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fanuraag-shukla.medium.com%2Fthe-rise-and-fall-of-atlas-cycles-1cd10628917%23%3A~%3Atext%3DJankidas%2520Kapoor%2520founded%2520Atlas%2520Cycle%2Ca%252025%252Dacre%2520factory%2520complex.%5C%22%3EAtlas%20Cycle%20Industries%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201951%20in%20Sonepat%2C%20Haryana.%20This%20local%20production%20marked%20a%20bicycle%20mania%20on%20Indian%20roads%20as%20they%20were%20produced%20in%20lakhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20437px)%2085vw%2C%20437px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122811%2FC1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22437%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122811%2FC1.jpg%20928w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122811%2FC1-232x300.jpg%20232w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122811%2FC1-792x1024.jpg%20792w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666075%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22565%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAffordable%20bicycles%20remade%20Indian%20cities%20as%20people%20accessed%20new%20spaces%20and%20moved%20between%20urban%20neighbourhoods%20for%20work%20and%20pleasure.%20In%20small%20towns%20and%20villages%20as%20well%2C%20the%20bicycle%20provided%20a%20new%20means%20for%20people%20to%20access%20work%20and%20social%20worlds.%20Bicycles%20have%20remained%20a%20symbol%20of%20economic%20and%20social%20mobility%20through%20the%20present%2C%20with%20grass%20roots%20political%20parties%20such%20as%20the%20Samajwadi%20Political%20Party%20embracing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-38635018%5C%22%3Ebicycle%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20their%20election%20symbol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20start%20of%20the%20cycle%20revolution%20in%20the%20late%2019th%20century%2C%20many%20mechanics%20were%20drawn%20from%20other%20artisan%20and%20craft%20worker%20backgrounds.%20They%20learned%20new%20skills%20specific%20to%20cycle%20repair%2C%20but%20also%20adapted%20long-standing%20mechanical%20skills%20from%20trades%20such%20as%20blacksmithing.%20Their%20forms%20of%20expertise%20kept%20Indians%20on%20the%20move%20throughout%20the%20twentieth%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earliest%20bicycles%20in%20India%20were%20objects%20of%20curiosity%20and%20leisure%2C%20imported%20and%20used%20by%20European%20colonialists%20and%20wealthy%20Indians%20beginning%20in%20the%201860s.%20Alongside%20these%20early%20cycles%20came%20a%20need%20to%20repair%20and%20maintain%20them.%20Racialized%20colonial%20hierarchies%20impacted%20early%20cycle%20mechanics%2C%20as%20some%20British%20cyclists%20in%20large%20cities%20such%20as%20Bombay%20clearly%20preferred%20European%20cycle%20mechanics.%20Throughout%20the%20late%20nineteenth-century%2C%20advertisements%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3Eboasted%20of%20%E2%80%98bicycles%20repaired%20by%20a%20skilled%20English%20mechanic%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20Indian%20craftworkers%2C%20artisans%2C%20and%20labourers%20rapidly%20adapted%20to%20the%20new%20industry%20and%20new%20technology%2C%20offering%20their%20skills%20to%20both%20European%20and%20Indian%20cyclists.%20Some%20of%20the%20earliest%20were%20employed%20directly%20by%20the%20merchants%20who%20imported%20and%20sold%20bicycles.%20The%20development%20of%20a%20skilled%20cadre%20of%20Indian%20cycle%20mechanics%20in%20major%20cities%20by%20the%201880s%20and%201890s%20allowed%20merchants%20and%20shopkeepers%20to%20provide%20%E2%80%98guarantees%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20cycles%20that%20they%20sold.%20Cycle%20merchants%20boasted%20of%20their%20%E2%80%98repair%20departments%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20were%20sometimes%20led%20by%20%E2%80%98European%20engineers%E2%80%99%20even%20as%20the%20physical%20work%20of%20repair%20was%20undertaken%20by%20Indian%20labourers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20men%20and%20women%20required%20repairs%20to%20their%20bicycles.%20In%20a%20fanciful%20story%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20of%20the%20Young%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Christian%20Association%20in%20Calcutta%20in%201899%2C%20a%20young%20woman%20imagined%20that%20her%20cycle%20came%20to%20life%20and%20spoke%20to%20her.%20After%20a%20pleasure%20ride%2C%20it%20admonished%20her%20for%20failing%20in%20its%20upkeep%2C%20saying%20%E2%80%98You%20forget%20I%20need%20to%20be%20well-oiled%20at%20regular%20intervals%2C%20and%20if%20I%20did%20not%20remind%20you%2C%20by%20this%20disagreeable%20noise%2C%20what%20a%20state%20I%20would%20get%20into!%E2%80%99%20Although%20this%20tale%20of%20the%20talking%20bicycle%20ultimately%20served%20as%20a%20Christian%20parable%2C%20reminding%20girls%20to%20pray%2C%20it%20also%20reflected%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20cycling%20%E2%80%93%20and%20bicycle%20maintenance%20%E2%80%93%20were%20part%20of%20the%20popular%20imagination%20by%20the%20turn%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201920s%2C%20cycles%20were%20increasingly%20accessible%20to%20people%20beyond%20the%20elite%20social%20classes%2C%20and%20cyclists%20developed%20new%20uses%20for%20the%20bicycle%20that%20often%20increased%20the%20need%20for%20repair.%20A%20municipal%20bylaw%20in%20Pune%20in%201929%20warned%20residents%20that%20%E2%80%98no%20person%20shall%20carry%20another%20person%20on%20an%20ordinary%20bicycle%E2%80%99%20within%20the%20municipality.%20Simultaneously%2C%20new%20provincial%20laws%20sought%20to%20tax%20goods%20%E2%80%98by%20the%20bicycle%20load%E2%80%99.%20These%20attempts%20to%20legislate%20what%20people%20carried%20on%20bicycles%20reflected%20the%20expanding%20use%20of%20the%20bicycle%2C%20as%20Indians%20turned%20to%20it%20to%20transport%20their%20families%2C%20friends%20and%20goods%2C%20rather%20than%20solely%20as%20a%20source%20of%20leisure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20468px)%2085vw%2C%20468px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122902%2FC2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122902%2FC2.jpg%20590w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122902%2FC2-220x300.jpg%20220w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666076%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22639%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%201975%20advertisement%20for%20Atlas%20bicycles%20in%20the%20Malabar%20Herald%20boasted%20of%20the%20quality%20of%20manufacturing%20and%20production%20(Malabar%20Herald%2C%2022%2F11%2F1975).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expanded%20use%20of%20the%20bicycle%20also%20included%20the%20development%20of%20the%20cycle%20rickshaw.%20Though%20first%20developed%20in%20the%201880s%2C%20cycle%20rickshaws%20were%20popularised%20across%20Asia%20in%20the%201920s%20and%201930s%2C%20first%20in%20Singapore%20and%20subsequently%20across%20South%20and%20South-East%20Asia.%20The%20evolution%20of%20new%20ways%20of%20using%20the%20bicycle%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20for%20the%20transport%20of%20goods%2C%20multiple%20people%2C%20or%20as%20a%20rickshaw%20%E2%80%93%20placed%20new%20pressures%20on%20its%20material%20and%20structure%2C%20and%20skilled%20bicycle%20mechanics%20were%20called%20upon%20to%20repair%20and%20maintain%20the%20machines%20when%20they%20faltered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20most%20prominent%20role%20for%20Indian%20bicycle%20mechanics%20before%20the%20mid%2020th%20century%20was%20in%20the%20repair%20and%20maintenance%20of%20bicycles%2C%20some%20were%20also%20employed%20with%20the%20production%20of%20and%20repair%20of%20component%20parts.%20As%20Arnold%20has%20shown%2C%20even%20before%20the%20foundation%20of%20large%20successful%20Indian%20bicycle%20manufacturers%20following%20the%20post-colonial%20import%20tariffs%20of%20the%201950s%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20manufacturers%20of%20components%20such%20as%20bells%2C%20stands%2C%20and%20carriers%20had%20become%20virtual%20cottage%20industries%E2%80%99%20in%20cities%20such%20as%20Ludhiana%20in%20Punjab.%20The%20manufacture%20of%20bicycle%20components%20remained%20a%20prominent%20industry%20in%20Punjab%20throughout%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20employing%2033%2C000%20people%20as%20of%201984%2C%20approximately%207%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98small%20sector%E2%80%99%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20number%20of%20small-scale%20Indian%20bicycle%20manufacturers%20operated%20in%20the%20interwar%20period%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpedalandtringtring.com%2F2019%2F12%2F13%2Fa-defunct-bicycle-factory%2F%5C%22%3EBirla%20Group%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%20cycle%20factory%20in%20Bombay%2C%20which%20later%20was%20nationalised%20and%20became%20the%20National%20Bicycle%20Corporation%20of%20India.%20The%20foundation%20of%20large-scale%20bicycle%20manufacturing%20works%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%20further%20expanded%20the%20demand%20for%20skilled%20cycle%20mechanics%2C%20with%20the%20Minister%20of%20Industry%20calling%20bicycle%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%98the%20fastest%20developing%20industry%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99%20in%201960.%20Classified%20ads%20from%20the%20period%20encouraged%20%E2%80%98technical%20personnel%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98general%20mechanics%E2%80%99%20to%20apply%20for%20employment%20in%20bicycle%20factories%20in%20cities%20such%20as%20Delhi.%20These%20workers%20primarily%20manufactured%20bicycles%20for%20the%20domestic%20market%2C%20though%20by%201979%2C%20India%20exported%20approximately%20355%2C000%20bicycles%20annually%2C%20out%20of%20approximately%20four%20million%20bicycles%20produced%20within%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122954%2FC3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22740%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122954%2FC3.jpg%20740w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01122954%2FC3-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666077%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22492%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%201896%20Urdu-English%20advertisement%20for%20cycles%20manufactured%20in%20Birmingham%20and%20sold%20in%20Calcutta%2C%20Madras%2C%20Bombay%20and%20Rangoon%20(Mirror%20of%20English%20Manufactures%2C%20April%201896).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBicycle%20manufacturing%20workshops%20thus%20expanded%20their%20demand%20for%20labor%20in%20mid-twentieth%20century%20India%2C%20drawing%20in%20fitters%2C%20metalsmiths%2C%20machinists%2C%20and%20other%20skilled%20Indian%20workers.%20Simultaneously%2C%20the%20work%20of%20cycle%20mechanics%20outside%20of%20these%20factories%20%E2%80%93%20often%20in%20small%20shops%2C%20stalls%2C%20or%20directly%20on%20the%20street%20%E2%80%93%20remained%20central%20to%20everyday%20transportation.%20A%201973%20report%20from%20Cochin%20described%20thick%20bicycle%20traffic%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20city%2C%20with%20pedestrian%20routes%20sometimes%20blocked%20by%20cycles%20parked%20at%20the%