%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31123657%2FUntitled-design-24-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20group%20of%20eight%20renowned%20writers%2C%20historians%20and%20artists%20have%20written%20to%20Tamil%20Nadu%20chief%20minister%20M.K.%20Stalin%20to%20express%20their%20concern%20about%20the%20arrest%20of%20publisher%20and%20writer%20Badri%20Seshadri%20for%20comments%20he%20made%20on%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeshadri%20was%20speaking%20of%20the%20CJI%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%2C%20and%20had%20questioned%20%E2%80%93%20referring%20to%20the%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20comment%20that%20the%20apex%20court%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20interfere%20in%20the%20issue%20if%20the%20Union%20government%20did%20not%20take%20appropriate%20action%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20judges%20have%20the%20knowledge%20of%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20ground%20realities%20to%20be%20able%20to%20judge%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20went%20on%20to%20question%20whether%20the%20CJI%20would%20dare%20to%20stand%20in%20Manipur%20wielding%20a%20gun%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFirst%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Ftamilnadu%2Fmadras-reporters-guild-condems-arrest-of-publisher-badri-seshadri-seeks-his-release%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20letter%20to%20Stalin%2C%20the%20signatories%20have%20said%20that%20while%20Seshadri%E2%80%99s%20comments%20may%20deserve%20%E2%80%9Cunequivocal%20condemnation%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Carrest%20is%20an%20extreme%20reaction%20to%20such%20an%20infringement%20and%20goes%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20constitutional%20assurance%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20letter%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Chief%20Minister%20Thiru.%20M.%20K.%20Stalin%20Avargal%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVanakkam%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20the%20undersigned%20write%20to%20draw%20your%20kind%20attention%20to%20the%20crucial%20question%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20ago%2C%20Thiru%20Badri%20Seshadri%2C%20publisher%20and%20writer%20has%20been%20arrested%20on%20the%20charge%20of%20holding%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20to%20contempt.%20There%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20Thiru%20Badri%20Seshadri%E2%80%99s%20outburst%20deserves%20unequivocal%20condemnation.%20However%2C%20we%20strongly%20believe%20that%20arrest%20is%20an%20extreme%20reaction%20to%20such%20an%20infringement%20and%20goes%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20constitutional%20assurance%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20believe%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20following%20the%20Dravidian%20Model%20of%20Governance%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20ideals%20of%20Thandai%20Periyar%2C%20Arignar%20Anna%20and%20Kalaignar%20Karunanidhi%20is%20strongly%20committed%20to%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20We%20expect%20the%20Government%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20which%20differs%20vastly%20from%20other%20state%20governments%20of%20the%20Indian%20union%2C%20to%20be%20an%20exemplary%20model%20in%20this%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThandai%20Periyar%20strongly%20urged%20the%20people%20to%20%E2%80%98not%20heed%20meaningless%20words%2C%20consider%20everything%20rationally%2C%20and%20act%20in%20a%20manner%20in%20conformity%20with%20reason.%E2%80%99%20Periyar%20not%20only%20advocated%20the%20right%20to%20expression%20but%20also%20the%20right%20to%20hear%20every%20point%20of%20view.%20Periyar%20trusted%20in%20the%20rationality%20of%20people%20and%20their%20ability%20to%20discriminate%20right%20from%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20therefore%20request%20you%20that%20Thiru%20Badri%20Seshadri%20be%20released%20at%20the%20earliest%20and%20encourage%20the%20refutation%20of%20his%20unacceptable%20views%20on%20various%20forums.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYours%20Sincerely%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignatories%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbai%2C%20Writer%3Cbr%3E%5CnPaul%20Zacharia%2C%20Writer%3Cbr%3E%5CnT.M.%20Krishna%2C%20Musician%3Cbr%3E%5CnPerumal%20Murugan%2C%20Writer%3Cbr%3E%5CnA.R.%20Venkatachalapathy%2C%20Historian%3Cbr%3E%5CnStalin%20Rajangam%2C%20Subaltern%20Historian%3Cbr%3E%5CnRajan%20Krishnan%2C%20Professor%3Cbr%3E%5CnKannan%20Sundaram%2C%20Publisher%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690864709000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31123657%2FUntitled-design-24-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Farrest-is-an-extreme-reaction-writers-artists-write-to-stalin-against-badri-seshadris-arrest%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Badri%20Seshadri%20was%20arrested%20for%20comments%20he%20made%20on%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Farrest-is-an-extreme-reaction-writers-artists-write-to-stalin-against-badri-seshadris-arrest%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple's%20main%20supplier%20Foxconn%20plans%20%24500%20mn%20component%20plants%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690864485000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-03%2F13%2Ffull%2F1647188469-6926.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fapple-s-main-supplier-foxconn-plans-500-mn-component-plants-in-india-123080100196_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Foxconn%20Technology%20Group%2C%20plans%20to%20increase%20its%20investments%20to%20more%20than%20%241.2%20bn%20in%20southern%20India's%20Karnataka%20state%20and%20add%20two%20component%20factories%2