ract%20with%20the%20school%20students.%20I%20realised%20the%20problems%20they%20face%2C%20even%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20doing%20simple%20things%20in%20society%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20making%20friends%20or%20finding%20good%20schools.%20I%20learnt%20that%20there%20are%20no%20avenues%20for%20them%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20come%20from%20the%20weaker%20sections%20of%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20began%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20with%20children%20who%20had%20autism%20and%20ADHD.%20I%20found%20out%20that%20they%20were%20so%20talented.%20Our%20society%20focuses%20so%20much%20on%20what%20is%20wrong%20that%20they%20forget%20to%20glance%20at%20the%20positive%20aspects.%20Most%20people%20consider%20the%20neurodivergent%20to%20be%20a%20burden%20or%20a%20liability.%20This%20restricts%20their%20opportunities%2C%20making%20their%20life%20harder%20than%20it%20should%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETarini%20shares%20that%20she%20has%20been%20working%20in%20the%20social%20sector%20from%20a%20very%20young%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20in%20Class%208%2C%20I%20volunteered%20as%20a%20teacher%20for%20a%20free%20school%20that%20taught%20children%20at%20the%20banks%20of%20Yamuna%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20good%20amount%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20field%2C%20Tarini%20felt%20it%20was%20the%20right%20time%20for%20her%20to%20start%20her%20own%20foundation.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20October%202020%2C%20I%20started%20the%20Nai%20Subah%20Foundation%20and%20decided%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20well-being%20of%20the%20neurodivergent%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Leave%20no%20one%20behind%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20foundation%20works%20for%20the%20neurodivergent%20through%20various%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETarini%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20thing%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20through%20the%20organisation%20