0England%2C%20Canada%20and%20other%20countries%20visit%20the%20school%20often%20as%20volunteers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEight%20students%2C%20a%20cow%20shed%20and%20teacher%20Aunty%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20started%20off%20really%20small%20with%20just%20eight%20students%20in%20a%20makeshift%20classroom%2C%20which%20was%20originally%20a%20cow%20shed.%20But%20this%20arrangement%20did%20not%20last%20long%20as%20we%20started%20to%20get%20more%20and%20more%20students%20every%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Lori.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20reason%20why%20I%20think%20we%20had%20such%20a%20big%20turnout%20was%20because%20the%20people%20here%20want%20to%20break%20the%20cycle%20of%20poverty.%20Their%20children%20who%20go%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F98044%2Fproject-kaleidoscope-taranagar-rajasthan-digital-education-piramal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20not%20able%20to%20face%20competition%20from%20children%20from%20private%20schools.%20They%20do%20not%20get%20admission%20to%20good%20colleges%20and%20many%20end%20up%20coming%20back%20to%20the%20villages%20to%20work%20on%20farms.%20The%20parents%20here%20really%20want%20their%20kids%20to%20come%20out%20of%20this%20cycle%20and%20earn%20a%20decent%20income.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20school%20had%20shifted%20to%20a%20bigger%20building%20with%20more%20teachers%20and%20amenities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fsaraam-3-1690289913.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20school%20runs%20from%20the%20proceeds%20from%20the%20cafe.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fsaraam-3-1690289913.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fsaraam-3-1690289913-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fsaraam-3-1690289913-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fsaraam-3-1690289913-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fsaraam-3-1690289913-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325108%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20students%20come%20from%20around%2025%20villages%20in%20the%20Jounpur%20Block%20of%20Tehri%20Garhwal.%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Lori%20Chauhan%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20we%20hired%20teachers%20from%20nearby%20areas.%20While%20they%20were%20educated%20enough%2C%20their%20method%20of%20teaching%20was%20the%20%E2%80%98jot-this-down-and-memorise-it%E2%80%99%20kind%20%E2%80%94%20just%20as%20they%20were%20taught%20in%20government%20schools.%20We%20did%20not%20want%20that%20for%20our%20school.%20So%20we%20started%20an%20outreach%20program%20and%20asked%20people%20from%20around%20the%20world%20to%20come%20and%20share%20their%20methods%20of%20teaching%20with%20our%20teachers%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Lori.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20quite%20a%20success%2C%20and%20we%20still%20have%20volunteers%20coming%20in%20from%20different%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20The%20school%20currently%20has%2013%20teachers%2C%20and%20the%20school%20is%20registered%20with%20the%20state%20education%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnother%20important%20aspect%20that%20we%20are%20very%20particular%20about%20is%20that%20all%20the%20learning%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20classrooms%20itself.%20Since%20the%20children%20here%20come%20from%20rural%20backgrounds%2C%20they%20do%20not%20have%20anyone%20